  "title": "Operational Due Diligence – Real Estate Investments",
  "description": "<ul><li>Established firm, strong branding</li><li>Career progression opportunities</li><li>Opportunity to work with senior stakeholders</li></ul><p>An Investment Firm is looking for an <strong>Operational Due Diligence Specialist </strong> to join their Private Equity Real Estate team.</p><p>This is a lean team of 2, supporting the Private Equity Real Estate, Operational Due Diligence (PERE ODD) business. You will be responsible for leading any governance-related initiatives for the PERE business. Working with both internal and external stakeholders to perform for the role, you will lead in ensuring that any JV vendor operational processes/practices are in line with regulatory and internal business standards. The role will require someone with an internal audit/controls/governance experience with a keen eye for identifying change initiatives.</p><p>The ideal candidate comes with 6 years relevant experience from an internal audit background, preferably from Real Estate/Funds/Asset Management. Strong communication skills and stakeholder management skills will be a pre-requisite for the role. Self starter, ability to work independently and be a strong team player at the same time.</p><p>If you are keen, please click on the link to apply or email me with your updated CV at Rachel.ljy@ethosbc.com. Look forward to hearing back, thank you.</p><p>Reg. No. R1987809<br />BeathChapman Pte Ltd<br />Licence no. 16S8112</p>",
